Hopes this helps.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Syll</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(10/20/00 8:13:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Exp penalty with pet</span><hr size=1> I have been camping the the Yetis at lv 41 in the Dreadlands. Leveled to 42 in about 4 hours I think. At first exp was slow because my fire pet was doing just over half damage (powerful little booger).  In this way, the pet uses up nearly half the exp from the kill. So I slowed down and would med up enough where I could cast one additional lower lv DD spell to do over half damage. (2 bolts and a shock of swords per yeti). Then my exp nearly double and I leveled faster by killing more slowly.<br>
<br>
bad exp = 2 bolts (666, less than half damage on yeti) and pet damage<br>
good exp = 2 bolts(666), shock of swords (176, just over half) and pet damage<br>
<br>
This goes for all level of mages vs slow big creatures. Send pet in, then blast from distance. If pet is about to die, it is preferable to take hits on yourself and blast monster with lower level (quick) spells. Healing pet is a waste of mana in a fight. If the pet is about to die, and you are low on mana, gate don't heal. I heal a earth pet after a fight if he is bad off (not at my current level though, they heal like crazy). Still, we don't have a good defense, so don't think defensive. Just kill as quick as possible. Killing is what we are most efficient at doing.<br>
<br>
Necro's and Druids are ok, but we deal fast damage. That is what a group depends on from us. Our healing power to a group comes from killing the mob before they can cause a lot of damage. So, we are popular in that respect. A wizard can root and cause a lot of damage, but I don't feel it is the same amount compared to us and our pet's combined damage in the same amount of time. <br>
<br>
Back to the lv 12 mage, I did very well in North Ro killing Dervs. Those weapons were about 4pp. After that, you forget about the cost of sumoning pets and buy food and water until you get cornicopia and everfount. around lv 15 group up and kill gators in Oasis until 16. THen go to Lavastorm. Cancel magic on elementals(cancels their flame shields) and earn exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglenfinen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glenfinen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(10/20/00 9:05:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Exp penalty with pet</span><hr size=1> Druids are excellent early but go downhill later on cuz it takes soo long to kite things with 2k hp.  I dont know, I just think kiting is so lame.<br>
<br>
Necros kill equally well all the way through.<br>
<br>
Mages, however, peak late and really shine at certain levels. 34(Kedge is nutty exp), 39+(pet regen is insane), 44-48(utter gods vs low blues with the fire pet), 49-52(still excellent but necro pets now catch up).  52+ down hill from there solo wise.  Blue mobs just hit way too hard at this level and the fear kite avoids so much damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill>The Hunt</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
